Quote:  <i>Kahawai Arripis trutta</i> ... Known principally by its Maori name, kahawai, in New Zealand and only occasionally (and erroneously, despite its scientific name) as sea trout or salmon. ... The name kopapa is sometimes given to the barred or spotted juveniles.
